    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-28T11:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-28T11:41:00-05:00" n="34"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1191</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-28T17:00:00+00:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.41 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1961. I learn that <persName corresp="#p_HCGFv1">Hertling</persName> told the
                    Dutch Minister at Berlin in answer to a question that he could riot have spoken
                    otherwise than he did [about] Belgium; that public opinion would not let him
                    promise the liberation of Belgium until promises had been made of the
                    restoration of the German colonies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
